text.text:
Paradise on hearth. Five star service 24h. Food is delicious. Room big and comfortable,  lots of pillows. You find whatever you need and more. We have been here already two times and we will come back soon.
The nature and the view here is unique, the most beautiful one, more than many others nearby. The staff is so kind and take care of you with love.

text.text: Our first time visiting Bali. So happy we chose Kayumanis Ubud for the most amazing experience. The private villa had plenty of space. The pool was gorgeous in a beautiful surrounding. Breakfasts and afternoon teas were very generous and delicious. The setting and surroundings are lush and quite. What made our trip so memorable and wanting to go back was the lovely staff of Kayumanis. Cannot fault them at all. From the front of house staff to the restaurant staff, they were so welcoming and warm. A highlight of our trip was the walk around the Rice Fields with Winda. Winda was happy to share her knowledge of the area, answered all our questions with grace and gave us insight into the local area. We'd like to thank all the staff at Kayumanis for making our stay so memorable. Special thank you to, Ode, Tagel, Winda, Suri, Sukarj and Kania. We also would like to do a special mention to local driver Krisna who was wonderful, happy to answer all our questions and give us a delightful insight to the local culture.

text.text:
Our stay at Kayumanis was amazing. From the moment we arrived, staff were ready to help and make our stay as comfortable as possible. Our villa was delightful with a large private pool, outdoor shower, huge outdoor pavilion and light filled bedroom.
We ate most of our meals at our villa but when we did eat at the dining corner and in other parts of the grounds it was lovely.
The food was great with very generous serving sizes and variety.
Thank you again for a wonderful stay!

Best place we have ever stayed. Instant relaxation. Villas are private and spacious.  Main pool is to die for.  Food is wonderful.  Most of all, never experienced customer service at this level even in the nicest 5 star hotels.

One small thing to be aware of - the site is somewhat steep so be ready for some exercise! Shuttle needed to get to Ubud but I personally like not being right in the middle of town.

We will definitely be returning any time we are in Ubud.

text.text:
A Thoughtfully Curated Eco-Friendly Dining Experience

From the moment you arrive, the staff welcomes you with warm hospitality, setting the tone for a memorable dining experience. The restaurant’s is beautifully reflected in its serene surroundings, offering breathtaking views that enhance the overall ambiance.

With a wide selection of gluten-free and vegan options. Every dish is thoughtfully prepared, emphasizing fresh, natural ingredients that align with their commitment to sustainability and wellness. Whether you’re seeking a nourishing meal or simply want to indulge in flavors that feel good, this is a must-visit destination in Ubud.

text.text:
River Warung Dayclub is an absolute paradise! Nestled within Bambu Indah, this bamboo-built, sustainable riverside restaurant offers a truly magical experience. Spending time here feels like escaping into a dream.

The atmosphere is simply breathtaking—lush greenery, a gentle breeze, and the soothing sound of the river create a setting that is nothing short of heavenly. The scenery alone is enough to leave you in awe!

The food was exceptional, fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented. The drinks were just as well-crafted, making the experience even more delightful. Plus, everything is served with sustainability in mind, adding even more value to the visit.

The service was flawless! A special shoutout to Aggna, who was incredibly kind and attentive. He made sure everything was perfect and truly enhanced our experience.

This place is more than just a restaurant—it's an immersive journey into nature, relaxation, and pure bliss. Highly recommended to anyone visiting Bali!

We arrived today and were BLOWN AWAY ❤️ the attention to detail in the resort’s design, the absolutely sweet and friendly staff, the amenities provided and the location 👌🏻 It’s truly a giant getaway hidden at the end of an unassuming alley overlooking beautiful paddy fields ❤️

text.text: Not the greatest pizza, but it hit the spot and filled us up cheap. Toppings tasty and diverse but the crust was disappointing. Friendly proprietors and pleasant seating on cushions  on the floor. We'll probably return in a while... Why are you eating pizza in Indonesia anyway? If you really want/need good pizza, go home already!

text.text: We called in and ordered a couple of large pizzas this evening. Wayan took our order and norhing was too much trouble for her. We wanted only a small amount of cheese, and the addition of fresh chilli. Order in and we went for a walk about for 20 minutes, and it was just coming out of the oven upon our return. Pizza was enjoyed on our villa verandah while watching the sun set and both were excellent! Only comments were that for us the less cheese was perfect, the chilli was very hot just as we like it, and next time I will ask for them to be cooked another 5 minutes, I suspect they came out of the oven sooner than usual due to us appearing for pick up, but the degree of cookedness is personal choice, they were perfectly good as presented. Highly recommended.
